Package Appointment

Interface AppointmentOutcomeService

All Known Implementing Classes:
AppointmentOutcomeManager
public interface AppointmentOutcomeService
The AppointmentOutcomeService interface provides methods for recording and viewing appointment outcomes and past records for patients.

This interface is designed to manage the outcome details of appointments, including services provided, medications prescribed, and consultation notes. It also allows for viewing past records and specific outcome records.

  • Method Details

    • recordAppointmentOutcome

      void recordAppointmentOutcome(String typeOfService, String prescribedMedication, String prescribedMedicationQuantity, String prescriptionStatus, String consultationNotes, String appointmentID)
      Records the outcome of an appointment, including details about the service provided, prescribed medication, and consultation notes.
      Parameters:
      typeOfService - The type of service provided during the appointment.
      prescribedMedication - The medication prescribed during the appointment.
      prescribedMedicationQuantity - The quantity of the prescribed medication.
      prescriptionStatus - The status of the prescription (e.g., "Fulfilled", "Pending").
      consultationNotes - Notes from the consultation.
      appointmentID - The ID of the appointment for which the outcome is being recorded.

    • viewPastRecords

      void viewPastRecords(String patientID)
      Views all past appointment records for a specific patient.
      Parameters:
      patientID - The ID of the patient whose past records are to be viewed.

    • viewOutcomeRecord

      void viewOutcomeRecord(String appointmentOutcomeID)
      Views the outcome record for a specific appointment outcome ID.
      Parameters:
      appointmentOutcomeID - The ID of the appointment outcome record to view.
